row.cell:
Quotes Nansen’s
                            note of Dec. 7: Norway accedes in part to U. S. trade proposals;
                            stipulated reservations.

list.item:
Prohibit the supply of coal as bunkers without the consent
                                        of the appropriate authority (e. g., the collector of
                                        customs);

Instruct the appropriate authority only to authorise the
                                        supply of bunkers to (1) Allied ships, (2) ships on the
                                        ships white list;

No articles of food as above described; metals; minerals;
                                        ores; sulphuric acid; wood pulp; horses; hides or skins;
                                        leather; wool; manufactures of the foregoing; or cotton
                                        goods of any kind, to be exported to enemy countries.

